magmakeys (0.7.0) unstable; urgency=low

  * renamed /etc/magmakeys/conf.d/ to /etc/magmakeys/keys.d/
    and argument -c/--configdir to -k/--keydir
  * split daemon into library files and main program
  * moved to version 0.7.0

 -- Stefan Tomanek <stefan@pico.ruhr.de>  Mon, 12 Oct 2009 11:47:53 +0200

magmakeys (0.6.1) unstable; urgency=low

  * fixed typo in error message
  * Added sorting of event handler names
  * added true statements to the end of each class
  * Added check after trying to open device files
  * added product info from HAL to DeviceFile object

 -- Stefan Tomanek <stefan@pico.ruhr.de>  Sun, 11 Oct 2009 13:35:07 +0200

magmakeys (0.6.0) unstable; urgency=low

  * magmakeys now reloads its config on receiving SIGHUP

 -- Stefan Tomanek <stefan@pico.ruhr.de>  Wed, 07 Oct 2009 13:56:20 +0200

magmakeys (0.5.1) unstable; urgency=low

  * --dump option now shows key combinations

 -- Stefan Tomanek <stefan@pico.ruhr.de>  Tue, 06 Oct 2009 16:28:46 +0200

magmakeys (0.5.0) unstable; urgency=low

  * added support for conf.d/ hotkey configuration
  * support for the configuration file /etc/magmakeys.conf has been removed, existing configurations
    can be preserved by simply moving them into /etc/magmakeys/conf.d/

 -- Stefan Tomanek <stefan@pico.ruhr.de>  Sun, 04 Oct 2009 22:54:52 +0200

